Booking Policy
1. Bookings cannot be confirmed until payment and a completed application form is received. Fees paid are non-
refundable (refer to terms and conditions of transfer/ cancellation policy).
Payment terms are:
a) 20% holding fee (i.e. Enrollment/ deposit) to reserve a seat and/or register interest in attending.
This payment must be done at least 21-28 working days (Saturday to Thursday) prior to programme
commencement or enrollment is deemed cancelled.
b) 100% payment prior to training delivery. It must be done at least 15 working days (Saturday to
Thursday) prior to the programme commencement or booking will be deemed cancelled and
cancellation policy below will apply.
2. Bookings reserved for participants outside Jordan must be accompanied by bank transfer (refer to bank transfer
details above).
3. Course fees include qualified & recognized instructor; instruction materials; certificates for all successful participants;
exams and examination fees (if applicable); pen/pencils, notepads.
4. Course fees do not include local travel costs or expenses.
5. Course fees include venue cost.
6. Course fees do not include hotel charges for the instructor(s) nor flights from their country of origin (if applicable).
7. Participants cannot bring any claim or legal action against Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited).
relating to participation in the programme or from knowledge obtained during the programme. The use of the
information or documentation obtained during the programme shall be at the users sole risk.
8. The invoice request must be signed by a manager who is authorized to release payment on behalf of the organization.
9. As soon as the course certificate is issued, it will be sent to the participant address mentioned above free of charge
within Jordan. Delivery fee will apply for sending certificate to an address located outside Jordan.
10. Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited). can quote participant as a reference even after the
agreement cancellation.

Transfer Policy
There will be no additional charge if an alternate/ substitute person wishes to replace the original participant. Please
inform us in writing of any changes to the original booking. However if a participant fails to attend the course, the fee
remains payable.
Cancellation Policy
Both parties have the right to cancel the agreement but retainers will be lost in such a cancellation. All cancellations
must be confirmed in writing to Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited). and the following applies:
a) 21-28 working days* before programme - 20% of Programme fee.
b) 11-20 working days* before Programme - 50% of Programme fee.
c) 1-10 working days* before Programme - 100% of programme fee.
(*) Working days are from Saturday to Thursday (9 AM - 17:30 PM)
Amendment Policy
1. Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited) reserves the right to change the published prices of any course
programme(s), or materials, or any course contents without prior notice.
2. Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited) reserves the right to cancel/ postpone a course at any time
without liability. In this case, participant will be offered an alternative date or a full refund of the course fees.
3. Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited) reserves the right to change the venue of the course facilitator
at any time, if needed.
4. Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited) reserves the right to change the announced instructor of the
course at any time, if needed.
Intellectual Copyright:
Client must respect Sharikat Tazweed Khadamat Al Jawda (QMSrs Limited) Intellectual Property Rights. They must not
modify the training material, sell or pass on to others all or part of the material in any way, shape or form.
